Name: LEA_base
EOL Comment: T4E2008 - Learned data#World#Lotus#Elise/Exige#2008-2011#MT#2kb#EEPROM#CRP#0x0#CroftT4E090

Name: CAL_base
EOL Comment: T4E2008#World#Lotus#Elise/Exige#2008-2011#MT#15540b#MPC563#CRP#0x3C8E#Lotus

Name: CAL_ecu_engine_speed_byte_coefficient
EOL Comment:
DO NOT EDIT THIS VALUE. Internal engine speed byte used within the ECU to index many lookup tables.

Formula: engine_speed = COEFFICIENT / flywheel_tooth_count_period - offset.

Name: CAL_ecu_engine_speed_byte_offset
EOL Comment:
DO NOT EDIT THIS VALUE. Internal engine speed byte used within the ECU to index many lookup tables.

Formula: engine_speed = coefficient / flywheel_tooth_count_period - OFFSET.

Name: CAL_sensor_baro_gain
EOL Comment: Barometric pressure sensor build into the ECU. Datasheet MXP4100A: 1/0.01059 * 10 mbar/kPa = 944

Name: CAL_sensor_baro_offset
EOL Comment: Barometric pressure sensor build into the ECU. Datasheet MXP4100A: 0.1518/0.01059 * 10 mbar/kPa = 143

Name: CAL_sensor_evap_gain
EOL Comment:
Pressure sensor calibration of the evaporative system.

Formula: pressure = signal * GAIN + offset

Name: CAL_sensor_evap_offset
EOL Comment:
Pressure sensor calibration of the evaporative system.

Formula: pressure = signal * gain + OFFSET

Name: CAL_sensor_map_gain
EOL Comment:
Pressure sensor calibration of the intake manifold.

Formula: pressure = signal * GAIN + offset

Name: CAL_sensor_map_offset
EOL Comment:
Pressure sensor calibration of the intake manifold.

Formula: pressure = signal * gain + OFFSET

Name: CAL_load_use_alphaN_timer
EOL Comment: Once the negative/positive tps change or the absolute tps threshold is triggered\, the alphaN will be used for this amount of time.

Name: CAL_misc_use_tmap
EOL Comment: On supercharged car\, there is an additional sensor build after the intercooler. 0 = Use temperature of MAF\, 1 = Use this sensor for engine air temperature.

Name: CAL_ign_cranking_max_runtime
EOL Comment: Time after startup to use the cranking ignition advance.

Name: CAL_sensor_dt_tps1_age
EOL Comment: Throttle body position differential value 1\, the current tps and an old tps values are used. This value sets how old should be the second value. Between 0 and 75ms.

Name: CAL_tc_rear_tyre_circumference
EOL Comment: Circumference of the rear tyres. Needed to convert the rotational speed of the wheels into a car speed.

Name: CAL_tc_abs_ring_teeth_count
EOL Comment: Number of teeth of holes of the abs ring. Needed to convert the abs signal into a rotational speed of the wheel.

Name: CAL_dfso_delay_recovery_multiplicator
EOL Comment: In certain conditions\, the DFSO delay is consumed. If this parameter is set to 1\, the delay will recover in the same amount of time that has been consumed.

Name: CAL_load_reactivity
EOL Comment:
Every 5ms\, the sampled load value (maf or alphaN) is mixed with the previous value.

Formula: value = (100% - REACTIVITY) * previous + REACTIVITY * sample

Name: CAL_ign_min_stop_coolant_to_use_adj2
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is below this startup temperature threshold\, adj2 is always 0.

Name: CAL_ign_max_stop_coolant_to_use_adj2
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is above this startup temperature threshold\, adj2 is always 0.

Name: CAL_ign_advance_dfso
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance (degree before top dead center) when dfso is activated.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (cranking): adv = ADVANCE_DFSO
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_injtip_in_adj_gears
EOL Comment:
Add extra fuel (injection time) based on change in the tps. It's like the accelerator pump of a carburator.

Formula: tip_in(t) = time_base * (dt_tps2 - (adj2 * t)) * adj1 * adj3 * ADJ_GEAR

Name: CAL_sensor_dt_engine_speed_age
EOL Comment: Engine speed differential\, the current speed and an old speed are used. This value sets how old should be the second value. Between 0 and 7 (7 is the less sensitive).

Name: CAL_knock_signal_avg_min
EOL Comment: Minimum value allowed for signal_avg.

Name: CAL_ign_advance_adj_cyl
EOL Comment: Ignition advance adjustment per cylinder.

Name: CAL_ac_disable_coolant
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is above this temperature threshold\, disable the A/C compressor.

Name: CAL_ac_enable_coolant
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is below this temperature threshold\, enable the A/C compressor.

Name: CAL_ac_disable_pps
EOL Comment: When the pps is above this position threshold\, disable the A/C compressor.

Name: CAL_ac_enable_tps
EOL Comment: When the tps is below this position threshold\, enable the A/C compressor.

Name: CAL_ac_disable_user_min_time
EOL Comment: Once the A/C is disabled by the user\, the A/C compressor will be held off at least this amount of time. Only afterwards it will be allowed to be turned back on.

Name: CAL_fan_low_on
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is above this temperature threshold\, turn on the low speed fan.

Name: CAL_fan_low_off
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is below this temperature threshold\, turn off the low speed fan.

Name: CAL_fan_low_on_engine_off
EOL Comment: WITH ENGINE OFF (HEAT SOAK): When the engine coolant is above this temperature threshold\, turn on the low speed fan.

Name: CAL_fan_low_off_engine_off
EOL Comment: WITH ENGINE OFF (HEAT SOAK): When the engine coolant is below this temperature threshold\, turn off the low speed fan.

Name: CAL_fan_high_on
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is above this temperature threshold\, turn on the high speed fan.

Name: CAL_fan_high_off
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is below this temperature threshold\, turn off the high speed fan.

Name: CAL_fan_cutoff
EOL Comment: When the car is above this speed threshold\, turn off the fan.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj1_corr_max_threshold
EOL Comment: The ECU will make a +10.24mg/s correction to the learned_flow_adj1 value\, if the flow_adj8 is above this threshold.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj1_corr_min_threshold
EOL Comment: The ECU will make a -10.24mg/s correction to the learned_flow_adj1 value\, if the flow_adj8 is below this threshold.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj1_corr_max
EOL Comment: Maximum learned_flow_adj1 value. The ECU will not make correction above this value.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj1_corr_min
EOL Comment: Minimum learned_flow_adj1 value. The ECU will not make correction below this value.

Name: CAL_closedloop_min_engine_air
EOL Comment: Minimum engine air temperature to enable the closed loop operation.

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_idle_time_between_step
EOL Comment:
WITH IDLING ENGINE: Minimum time between stft corrections. At 1200rpm.

Formula: time = TIME_BETWEEN_STEP * 1200 / engine_speed

Name: CAL_ac_disable_engine_speed
EOL Comment: When the engine is above this speed threshold\, disable the A/C compressor.

Name: CAL_ac_enable_engine_speed
EOL Comment: When the engine is below this speed threshold\, enable the A/C compressor.

Name: CAL_ac_disable_pps_min_time
EOL Comment: If the A/C compressor is disabled by the pps position threshold\, it will be held off for at least this amount of time.

Name: CAL_ac_enable_user_min_time
EOL Comment: Once the A/C is enabled by the user\, the A/C compressor will be held on at least this amount of time. Only afterwards it will be allowed to be turned back off.

Name: CAL_misc_recirculation_pump_on_engine_off
EOL Comment: WITH ENGINE OFF (HEAT SOAK): When the engine coolant is above this temperature threshold\, turn on the recirculation pump.

Name: CAL_misc_recirculation_pump_off_engine_off
EOL Comment: WITH ENGINE OFF (HEAT SOAK): When the engine coolant is below this temperature threshold\, turn off the recirculation pump.

Name: CAL_load_alphaN_adj_corr_max
EOL Comment: Maximum alphaN adj value. The ECU will not make correction above this value.

Name: CAL_load_alphaN_adj_corr_min
EOL Comment: Minimum alphaN adj value. The ECU will not make correction below this value.

Name: CAL_tc_car_speed_reactivity
EOL Comment:
At every cycle\, the sampled car speed value is mixed with the previous value.

Formula: value = (100% - REACTIVITY) * previous + REACTIVITY * sample

Name: CAL_load_alphaN_adj_corr_min_coolant
EOL Comment: The ECU will not make correction to the alphaN adj table\, unless the engine coolant is above this temperature threshold.

Name: CAL_fan_high_off_user_delay
EOL Comment: The signal AC REQ FAN also controls the high speed fan. But when this signal is deasserted\, a delay defined by this value is used before the fan is turned off.

Name: CAL_sensor_engine_air_reactivity
EOL Comment:
At every cycle\, the sampled engine air value is mixed with the previous value.

Formula: value = (100% - REACTIVITY) * previous + REACTIVITY * sample

Name: CAL_sensor_coolant_reactivity
EOL Comment:
At every cycle\, the sampled coolant value is mixed with the previous value.

Formula: value = (100% - REACTIVITY) * previous + REACTIVITY * sample

Name: CAL_sensor_intake_air_reactivity
EOL Comment:
At every cycle\, the sampled intake air value is mixed with the previous value.

Formula: value = (100% - REACTIVITY) * previous + REACTIVITY * sample

Name: CAL_sensor_fuel_reactivity
EOL Comment:
At every cycle\, the sampled fuel level value is mixed with the previous value.
Note: This does not have an influence on the fuel gauge of the instrument cluster.

Formula: value = (100% - REACTIVITY) * previous + REACTIVITY * sample

Name: CAL_ac_disable_car_speed
EOL Comment: When the car is above this speed threshold\, disable the A/C compressor.

Name: CAL_ac_enable_car_speed
EOL Comment: When the car is below this speed threshold\, enable the A/C compressor.

Name: CAL_ecu_ign_threshold
EOL Comment: By turning the key on the IGN position\, power is asserted to a dedicated input of the ECU and is considered active if above this threshold.

Name: CAL_dfso_enable_car_speed
EOL Comment: When the car is above this speed threshold\, enable the deceleration fuel shut off.

Name: CAL_dfso_disable_car_speed
EOL Comment: When the car is below this speed threshold\, disable the deceleration fuel shut off.

Name: CAL_sensor_O2_heater_warmup_period
EOL Comment: The duty cylce is hard coded to 80% but the period can be changed.

Name: CAL_sensor_O2_heater_warmup_time
EOL Comment: Once the engine is running and during this WARMUP time\, the O2 heater will be progressively heated up (80% heater duty cycle).

Name: CAL_knock_retard1_limit
EOL Comment: Maximium allowed value for retard1.

Name: CAL_knock_retard2_corr_inc_coef
EOL Comment:
The ECU will make corrections to the retard2 value\, if the engine load is above the retard2_corr_threshold.

Formula (retard1 is 0): retard2 = retard2 - retard2_corr_dec_step
Formula (retard1  > 0): retard2 = retard2 + retard1 * RETARD2_CORR_INC_COEF

Note: retard2 is saved in the eeprom.

Name: CAL_knock_retard2_corr_dec_step
EOL Comment:
The ECU will make corrections to the retard2 value\, if the engine load is above the retard2_corr_threshold.

Formula (retard1 is 0): retard2 = retard2 - RETARD2_CORR_DEC_STEP
Formula (retard1  > 0): retard2 = retard2 + retard1 * retard2_corr_inc_coef

Note: retard2 is saved in the eeprom.

Name: CAL_knock_retard1_engine_speed_max
EOL Comment: If the engine is above this speed threshold\, disable retard1. It will be re-enable when the engine speed will be below this threshold minus the speed_margin.

Name: CAL_knock_retard1_engine_speed_min
EOL Comment: If the engine is below this speed threshold\, disable retard1. It will be re-enable when the engine speed will be above this threshold plus the speed_margin.

Name: CAL_knock_retard1_min_coolant
EOL Comment: If the engine coolant is below this temperature threshold\, disable retard1.

Name: CAL_knock_signal_fadeout_step
EOL Comment:
WHEN KNOCK IS DETECTED: Fadeout the peak by incrementing the average.

Formula: signal_avg = signal_avg + SIGNAL_FADEOUT_STEP

Name: CAL_knock_signal_reactivity
EOL Comment:
To separate real knock from noise\, a peak detection is build for every cylinders.

Formula:

signal_avg = (100% - REACTIVITY) * signal_avg + REACTIVITY * signal
peak = (signal * 10) / (signal_avg + 1)
peak_over_threshold = peak - threshold

Name: CAL_knock_speed_margin
EOL Comment: Engine speed margin for retard1_engine_speed_min and retard1_engine_speed_max thresholds.

Name: CAL_knock_load_margin
EOL Comment: Engine load margin for retard_threshold and retard2_corr_threshold thresholds.

Name: CAL_knock_retard1_dt_tps2_time
EOL Comment: If the retard1 is disabled by a change in tps\, it will be re-enable after this amount of time.

Name: CAL_knock_retard1_dt_tps2_threshold
EOL Comment: If the tps is above this change threshold\, disable retard1.

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_avg_reactivity
EOL Comment:
Every 5ms\, the stft value is mixed with the previous value to build an average. The stft average is then used in the ltft.

Formula: value = (100% - REACTIVITY) * previous + REACTIVITY * sample

Name: CAL_evap_enable_inj_time_threshold
EOL Comment: When the INJECTION TIME and idle flow are above their respective thresholds\, enable the evaporative canister purge.

Name: CAL_evap_disable_inj_time_threshold
EOL Comment: When the injection is below this time threshold\, disable the evaporative canister purge.

Name: CAL_evap_enable_idle_flow_threshold
EOL Comment: When the injection time and IDLE FLOW are above their respective thresholds\, enable the evaporative canister purge.

Name: CAL_evap_disable_idle_flow_threshold
EOL Comment: When the idle is below this flow threshold\, disable the evaporative canister purge.

Name: CAL_fan_high_on_ac_on
EOL Comment: WITH A/C ON: When the engine coolant is above this temperature threshold\, turn on the high speed fan.

Name: CAL_fan_high_off_ac_on
EOL Comment: WITH A/C ON: When the engine coolant is below this temperature threshold\, turn off the high speed fan.

Name: CAL_ign_advance_idle_adj_ac_on
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance adjustment when A/C is on.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + IDLE_ADJ_AC_ON
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_ign_advance_min
EOL Comment: Minimum allowable ignition advance.

Name: CAL_injtip_in_adj_gears_6
EOL Comment:
Add extra fuel (injection time) based on change in the tps. It's like the accelerator pump of a carburator.

Formula: tip_in(t) = time_base * (dt_tps2 - (adj2 * t)) * adj1 * adj3 * ADJ_GEAR

Name: CAL_sensor_engine_speed_period_avg_size
EOL Comment: Sometimes an average is used on the sampled engine speed period values. This value sets how many samples are used to build the average. Between 1 and 7 (1 no average\, 7 very smooth).

Name: CAL_inj_afr_adj_per_advance_adj
EOL Comment:
Fuel enrichment based on ignition advance (No enleanment allowed).

Formula:

afr_adj = AFR_ADJ_PER_ADVANCE_IGNITION_ADJ * (knock_ign_retard2 - ign_advance_adj1 - ign_advance_adj3)

a = (load / (afr_base - afr_adj)) - evap
b = a / (efficiency * flow_rate)
c = b * adj1 * adj2 * adj3 + tip_in + tip_out + reactive
d = base + ltft_idle + (1 + stft + 2 * ltft) * c

inj_time = d

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_idle_step
EOL Comment:
Decrement/Increment for the ltft correction when idling.

Formula (idle): idle_adj = idle_adj -/+ IDLE_STEP

Name: CAL_sensor_pps1_gain
EOL Comment:
Pedal position sensor 1 calibration.

Formula: pps1 = GAIN * (signal - offset)

Name: CAL_sensor_pps2_gain
EOL Comment:
Pedal position sensor 2 calibration. There is 2 potentiometers in the gas pedal for redundancy. The second is usually half of the first.

Formula: pps2 = GAIN * (signal - offset)

Name: CAL_sensor_pps_reactivity
EOL Comment:
Every 5ms\, the sampled pps value is mixed with the previous value.

Formula: value = (100% - REACTIVITY) * previous + REACTIVITY * sample

Name: CAL_sensor_map_avg_size
EOL Comment: An average is used on the sampled MAP values. This value sets how many samples are used to build the average. Between 1 and 31 (1 no average\, 31 very smooth).

Name: CAL_tc_front_tyre_circumference
EOL Comment: Circumference of the front tyres. Needed to convert the rotational speed of the wheels into a car speed.

Name: CAL_tc_mode
EOL Comment: Traction control mode: 0 = no traction control\, 1 = normal traction control\, 2 = variable traction control.

Name: CAL_tc_slip_adj2
EOL Comment:
When the car is slipping the ecu apply a factor to the advance of the ignition. A retard to the ignition makes the engine loose torque.

Formula: ign_adv_adj = 100% - steps - (slip - adj1 - ADJ2) * slip_to_retard_ratio

Name: CAL_tc_max_front_speed
EOL Comment: When the car is above this speed threshold\, disable the traction control.

Name: CAL_tc_min_front_speed
EOL Comment: When the car is below this speed threshold\, disable the traction control.

Name: CAL_tc_min_engine_speed
EOL Comment: When the engine is below this speed threshold\, disable the traction control.

Name: CAL_tc_slip_adj2_enable_left_right_threshold
EOL Comment: When the difference between left and right wheel (front or rear axle) is above this speed threshold\, the adj2 is immediately enable.

Name: CAL_tc_slip_adj2_disable_delay
EOL Comment: The adj2 is disable after this amount of time.

Name: CAL_tc_time_between_step
EOL Comment:
When the car is slipping\, steps is increment at this time interval. And once the car is stabilised\, steps is also decrement at this time interval.

Formula: ign_adv_adj = 100% - STEPS - (slip - adj1 - adj2) * slip_to_retard_ratio

Name: CAL_tc_min_slip
EOL Comment:
When the slip is above this value threshold\, activate the traction control.

Formula: slip = wheel_speed_rear / wheel_speed_front

Name: CAL_tc_slip_to_retard_ratio
EOL Comment:
When the car is slipping the ecu apply a factor to the advance of the ignition. A retard to the ignition makes the engine loose torque.

Formula: ign_adv_adj = 100% - steps - (slip - adj) * SLIP_TO_RETARD_RATIO

Name: CAL_tc_ign_advance_adj_limit
EOL Comment: Maximum ignition retard allowed for traction control.

Name: CAL_tc_slip_reactivity
EOL Comment:
At every cycle\, the sampled slip value is mixed with the previous value.

Formula: value = (100% - REACTIVITY) * previous + REACTIVITY * sample

Name: CAL_ign_advance_idle_adj3_dt_engine_speed_age
EOL Comment: Engine speed differential\, the current speed and an old speed are used. This value sets how old should be the second value. Between 0 and 10 (10 is the less sensitive).

Name: CAL_idle_flow_base
EOL Comment:
Compute the needed engine power (air flow) to keep a stabilized idling.

Formula: flow = FLOW_BASE + learned_adj1 - adj2 + adj3 + (adj4 * adj4_adj) + adj5 + adj6 + adj7 + adj8 + adj_ac + adj_fan_low + adj_fan_high - evap_flow

Note: adj8 is a dynamic adjustment.

Name: CAL_ecu_startrelay_max_runtime
EOL Comment: When the engine has run longer than this time threshold\, disable the start relay.

Name: CAL_evap_period
EOL Comment: TODO: Check scale\, it could be u16_time_50ns too.

Name: CAL_load_alphaN_adj_corr_limit_dt_engine_speed
EOL Comment: The ECU will not make correction to the alphaN adj table\, if the negative or positive engine speed change is above this limit threshold.

Name: CAL_misc_engine_detection_on
EOL Comment: When the engine is above this speed threshold\, the engine is considered as started.

Name: CAL_misc_engine_detection_off
EOL Comment: When the engine is below this speed threshold\, the engine is considered as stopped.

Name: CAL_fan_high_off_min_time
EOL Comment: The high speed fan will be held off for at least this amount of time. Only afterwards it will be allowed to be turned back on.

Name: CAL_misc_gears
EOL Comment: The ECU estimates the current gear based on rpm and vehicle speed and these are the thresholds for that determination.

Name: CAL_closedloop_afr
EOL Comment: Target afr value to enable the closed loop operation.

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_limit
EOL Comment: Maximum allowed negative or positive value for stft.

Name: CAL_fan_low_off_min_time
EOL Comment: The low speed fan will be held off for at least this amount of time. Only afterwards it will be allowed to be turned back on.

Name: CAL_ecu_fuelpump_prime
EOL Comment: When the ignition is switched on\, the ECU energises the fuel pump during this amount of time to prime the system before switching off.

Name: CAL_sensor_pps1_offset
EOL Comment:
Pedal position sensor 1 calibration.

Formula: pps1 = gain * (signal - OFFSET)

Name: CAL_ac_min_runtime
EOL Comment: The engine has to be running at least this amount of time\, before the A/C compressor can be turned on.

Name: CAL_load_alphaN_adj_corr_time_between_step
EOL Comment: Minimum time between ECU correction of the alphaN adj table.

Name: CAL_load_alphaN_adj_corr_high_threshold
EOL Comment: The ECU will make a -1% correction to the alphaN adj table\, if the ratio between the alphaN and the maf load is above this threshold.

Name: CAL_load_alphaN_adj_corr_low_threshold
EOL Comment: The ECU will make a +1% correction to the alphaN adj table\, if the ratio between the alphaN and the maf load is below this threshold.

Name: CAL_load_alphaN_adj_corr_min_time
EOL Comment: Once the ECU is allowed to make corrections to the alphaN adj table\, wait this amount of time before the first correction.

Name: CAL_sensor_pps2_offset
EOL Comment:
Pedal position sensor 2 calibration. There is 2 potentiometers in the gas pedal for redundancy.

Formula: pps2 = gain * (signal - OFFSET)

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj8_corr_time_between_step
EOL Comment: Minimum time between ECU correction of the flow_adj8 value.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj8_corr_max
EOL Comment: Maximum flow_adj8 value. The ECU will not make correction above this value.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj8_corr_min
EOL Comment: Minimum flow_adj8 value. The ECU will not make correction below this value.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj5_threshold
EOL Comment:
When the car is below this speed threshold\, the flow_adj5 will be used.

Note: The ignition adj1_alternative will also be used instead of adj1.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_pps_threshold
EOL Comment: When the pps is above this position threshold\, disble the correction of the adj1_learned\, adj8 and more...

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj7_disable_threshold
EOL Comment:
When the engine speed is below the target_speed+threshold\, the flow_adj7 is disable.

Note: Between the disable and enable threshold\, adj7 is factorized.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj7_enable_threshold
EOL Comment:
When the engine speed is above the target_speed+threshold\, the flow_adj7 is enable.

Note: Between the disable and enable threshold\, adj7 is factorized.

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_enrichment_step_adj
EOL Comment:
When a lean condition is detected\, the stft will enrich the mixture.

Formula (first)     : stft = stft + initial
Formula (subsequent): stft = stft + step
Formula (with adj)  : stft = stft + step * ADJ

Name: CAL_sensor_maf_avg_size
EOL Comment: An average is used on the sampled maf values. This value sets how many samples are used to build the average. Between 1 and 31 (1 no average\, 31 very smooth).

Name: CAL_idle_flow_time_between_decrement
EOL Comment: When the flow is reduced\, it will be smoothly decremented (-0.1g/s) using the flow_time_between_decrement time interval.

Name: CAL_injtip_time_base
EOL Comment: Standard: 60us for 330cc/min and 40us for 440cc/min injector.

Name: CAL_sensor_dt_tps2_age
EOL Comment: Throttle body position differential value 2\, the current tps and an old tps values are used. This value sets how old should be the second value. Between 0 and 75ms.

Name: CAL_injtip_in_dt_tps2_limit
EOL Comment:
Positive limit value for dt_tps2. 

Formula: tip_out(t) = time_base * (DT_TPS2 - (adj2 * t)) * adj1 * adj3

Name: CAL_injtip_in_dt_tps2_threshold
EOL Comment: Minimal dt_tps2 value to trigger the tip-in algorithm (t = 0).

Name: CAL_injtip_out_dt_tps2_limit
EOL Comment:
Negative limit value for dt_tps2. 

Formula: tip_out(t) = time_base * (DT_TPS2 - (adj2 * t)) * adj1 * adj3

Name: CAL_injtip_out_dt_tps2_threshold
EOL Comment: Minimal dt_tps2 value to trigger the tip-out algorithm (t = 0).

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_time_between_step
EOL Comment: Minimum time between stft corrections.

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_enleanment_step_adj
EOL Comment:
When a rich condition is detected\, the stft will enlean the mixture.

Formula (first)     : stft = stft - initial
Formula (subsequent): stft = stft - step
Formula (with adj)  : stft = stft - step * ADJ

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_min_engine_air
EOL Comment: Minimum engine air temperature to enable the ltft correction.

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_min_fuel
EOL Comment: Minimum fuel level to enable the ltft correction.

Name: CAL_misc_tps_max
EOL Comment: Maximum target tps position (including the idle target tps position).

Name: CAL_misc_tps_min
EOL Comment: Minimum target tps position (including the idle target tps position).

Name: CAL_idle_tps_max
EOL Comment:
Maximum allowed tps position for idling.

Note: tps_max does not limit the tps engine stop value.

Name: CAL_dfso_disable_pps
EOL Comment: When the pps is below this position threshold\, disable the deceleration fuel shut off.

Name: CAL_dfso_enable_pps
EOL Comment: When the pps is above this position threshold\, enable the deceleration fuel shut off.

Name: CAL_dfso_enable_engine_speed
EOL Comment: When the engine is above this speed threshold\, enable the deceleration fuel shut off.

Name: CAL_dfso_disable_engine_speed
EOL Comment: When the engine is below this speed threshold\, disable the deceleration fuel shut off.

Name: CAL_dfso_enable_coolant
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is above this temperature threshold\, enable the deceleration fuel shut off.

Name: CAL_dfso_disable_coolant
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is below this temperature threshold\, disable the deceleration fuel shut off.

Name: CAL_idle_speed_time_between_decrement
EOL Comment: Desired engine idle speed. When the speed is reduced\, it will be smoothly decremented (-10rpm) using the speed_time_between_decrement time interval.

Name: CAL_injtip_catalyst_adj_fadeout
EOL Comment:
During DFSO the catalyst is oxidized. Add extra fuel (injection time) to reactivate the catalyst.

Formula: reactivate = (time_base * adj) * (ADJ_FADEOUT ^ t)

Name: CAL_dfso_min_runtime
EOL Comment: Minimum engine run time to allow deceleration fuel shut off.

Name: CAL_load_use_alphaN_speed_limit
EOL Comment: When the engine is above this speed limit\, ignore the alphaN table (only maf).

Name: CAL_load_use_alphaN_dt_tps1_negative_threshold
EOL Comment: When the negative tps change (dt_tps1) is above this threshold\, use the alphaN load calculation.

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_min_atmo
EOL Comment: Minimum atmospheric pressure to enable the ltft correction.

Name: CAL_evap_duty_cycle_max
EOL Comment: Maximum allowed duty cycle for purge.

Name: CAL_evap_duty_cycle_min
EOL Comment: Minimum allowed duty cycle for purge.

Name: CAL_vvt_period
EOL Comment: Period of the pwm signal for the vvt.

Name: CAL_vvl_period
EOL Comment: Period of the pwm signal for the vvl.

Name: CAL_vvl_enable_rpm
EOL Comment: When the engine is above this speed threshold\, engage the vvl.

Name: CAL_vvl_disable_rpm
EOL Comment: When the engine is below this speed threshold\, disengage the vvl.

Name: CAL_vvl_enable_coolant
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is above this temperature threshold\, enable the vvl.

Name: CAL_vvl_disable_coolant
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is below this temperature threshold\, disable the vvl.

Name: CAL_vvl_enable_duty_cycle
EOL Comment: Duty cycle of the pwm signal for the engaged vvl.

Name: CAL_vvl_disable_duty_cycle
EOL Comment: Duty cycle of the pwm signal for the disengaged vvl.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj1_corr_min_maf_accumulated
EOL Comment: The ECU will not make correction to the learned_flow_adj1 value\, unless the air is above this mass threshold.

Name: CAL_load_alphaN_adj_corr_limit_dt_tps
EOL Comment: The ECU will not make correction to the alphaN adj table\, if the negative or positive tps change is above this limit threshold.

Name: CAL_load_use_alphaN_dt_tps1_positive_threshold
EOL Comment: When the positive tps change (dt_tps1) is above this threshold\, use the alphaN load calculation.

Name: CAL_misc_gears_6
EOL Comment: Thresholds for the 6th gear.

Name: CAL_idle_speed_adj_ac_on
EOL Comment:
Desired engine idle speed.

Formula: speed_target = speed_base + speed_adj + SPEED_ADJ_AC_ON

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_idle_max_flow_threshold
EOL Comment:
The ltft has 3 distincts ranges. The first range is when the engine is idling\, the second for low power and the third for high power.

This threshold defines the maximum maf flow for the idle range.

Formula (idle)      : ltft = 100%
Formula (low range) : ltft = low_adj
Formula (between)   : ltft = (low_adj * low_ratio) + (high_adj * high_ratio)
Formula (high range): ltft = high_adj

low_ratio = (maf - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)
high_ratio = (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - maf) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)

Note: low_adj and high_adj are saved in the eeprom.

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_idle_max_engine_speed_threshold
EOL Comment:
The ltft has 3 distincts ranges. The first range is when the engine is idling\, the second for low power and the third for high power.

This threshold defines the maximum engine speed for the idle range.

Formula (idle)      : ltft = 100%
Formula (low range) : ltft = low_adj
Formula (between)   : ltft = (low_adj * low_ratio) + (high_adj * high_ratio)
Formula (high range): ltft = high_adj

low_ratio = (maf - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)
high_ratio = (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - maf) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)

Note: low_adj and high_adj are saved in the eeprom.

EOL Comment:
The ltft has 3 distincts ranges. The first range is when the engine is idling\, the second for low power and the third for high power.

This threshold defines the maximum maf flow for the low range.

Formula (idle)      : ltft = 100%
Formula (low range) : ltft = low_adj
Formula (between)   : ltft = (low_adj * low_ratio) + (high_adj * high_ratio)
Formula (high range): ltft = high_adj

high_ratio = (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - maf) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)

Note: low_adj and high_adj are saved in the eeprom.

EOL Comment:

This threshold defines the minimum maf flow for the low range.

Formula (idle)      : ltft = 100%

Formula (high range): ltft = high_adj

low_ratio = (maf - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)
high_ratio = (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - maf) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)

Note: low_adj and high_adj are saved in the eeprom.

This threshold defines the maximum engine load for the low range.

Formula (idle)      : ltft = 100%
Formula (low range) : ltft = low_adj
Formula (between)   : ltft = (low_adj * low_ratio) + (high_adj * high_ratio)
Formula (high range): ltft = high_adj

low_ratio = (maf - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)
high_ratio = (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - maf) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)

Note: low_adj and high_adj are saved in the eeprom.

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_low_min_load_threshold
EOL Comment:
The ltft has 3 distincts ranges. The first range is when the engine is idling\, the second for low power and the third for high power.

This threshold defines the minimum engine load for the low range.

Formula (idle)      : ltft = 100%
Formula (low range) : ltft = low_adj
Formula (between)   : ltft = (low_adj * low_ratio) + (high_adj * high_ratio)
Formula (high range): ltft = high_adj

low_ratio = (maf - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)
high_ratio = (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - maf) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)

EOL Comment:
The ltft has 3 distincts ranges. The first range is when the engine is idling\, the second for low power and the third for high power.

Formula (idle)      : ltft = 100%
Formula (low range) : ltft = low_adj
Formula (between)   : ltft = (low_adj * low_ratio) + (high_adj * high_ratio)

low_ratio = (maf - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)
high_ratio = (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - maf) / (ltft_high_min_flow_threshold - ltft_low_max_flow_threshold)

EOL Comment:
The ltft has 3 distincts ranges. The first range is when the engine is idling\, the second for low power and the third for high power.

This threshold defines the minimum engine load for the high range.

Formula (idle)      : ltft = 100%
Formula (low range) : ltft = low_adj
Formula (between)   : ltft = (low_adj * low_ratio) + (high_adj * high_ratio)

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_min_coolant
EOL Comment: Minimum engine coolant temperature to enable the ltft correction.

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_time_between_step
EOL Comment: Minimum time between ltft corrections.

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_stft_avg_high_threshold
EOL Comment:
When the average stft is above this correction threshold\, the ltft is incremented.

Formula (idle)      : idle_adj = idle_adj + idle_step
Formula (low range) : low_adj = low_adj + 0.2%
Formula (between)   : -
Formula (high range): high_adj = high_adj + 0.2%

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_stft_avg_low_threshold
EOL Comment:
When the average stft is below this correction threshold\, the ltft is decremented.

Formula (idle)      : idle_adj = idle_adj - idle_step
Formula (low range) : low_adj = low_adj - 0.2%
Formula (between)   : -
Formula (high range): high_adj = high_adj - 0.2%

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_idle_max
EOL Comment: Maximum allowed value for idle_adj.

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_idle_min
EOL Comment: Minimum allowed value for idle_adj.

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_low_max
EOL Comment: Maximum allowed value for low_adj.

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_low_min
EOL Comment: Minimum allowed value for low_adj.

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_high_max
EOL Comment: Maximum allowed value for high_adj.

Name: CAL_closedloop_ltft_high_min
EOL Comment: Minimum allowed value for high_adj.

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_idle_enrichment_step
EOL Comment:
WITH IDLING ENGINE: When a lean condition is detected\, the stft will enrich the mixture.

Formula (first)     : stft = stft + initial
Formula (subsequent): stft = stft + STEP

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_idle_enleanment_step
EOL Comment:
WITH IDLING ENGINE: When a rich condition is detected\, the stft will enlean the mixture.

Formula (first)     : stft = stft - initial
Formula (subsequent): stft = stft - STEP

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_idle_enrichment_initial
EOL Comment:
WITH IDLING ENGINE: When a lean condition is detected\, the stft will enrich the mixture.

Formula (first)     : stft = stft + INITIAL
Formula (subsequent): stft = stft + step

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_idle_enleanment_initial
EOL Comment:
WITH IDLING ENGINE: When a rich condition is detected\, the stft will enlean the mixture.

Formula (first)     : stft = stft - INITIAL
Formula (subsequent): stft = stft - step

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_rich_threshold
EOL Comment: When the pre O2 sensor is above this voltage threshold\, a rich condition is detected and the stft will enlean the mixture.

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_lean_threshold
EOL Comment: When the pre O2 sensor is below this voltage threshold\, a lean condition is detected and the stft will enrich the mixture.

Name: CAL_inj_flow_rate
EOL Comment:
Injector size: 4600mg/s = 330cc/min and 6200mg/s = 440cc/min. This parameter doesn't affect the tip-in/out value\, change the base time of tip accordingly.

Formula:

a = (load / (afr_base - afr_adj)) - evap
b = a / (efficiency * FLOW_RATE)
c = b * adj1 * adj2 * adj3 + tip_in + tip_out + reactive
d = base + ltft_idle + (1 + stft + 2 * ltft) * c

inj_time = d

Name: CAL_misc_airbox_flap_close
EOL Comment: When the engine is below this speed threshold\, close the flap in the airbox.

Name: CAL_misc_airbox_flap_open
EOL Comment: When the engine is above this speed threshold\, open the flap in the airbox.

Name: CAL_vvl_enable_rpm_high_load
EOL Comment: HIGH LOAD: When the engine is above this speed threshold\, engage the vvl.

Name: CAL_vvl_disable_rpm_high_load
EOL Comment: HIGH LOAD: When the engine is below this speed threshold\, disengage the vvl.

Name: CAL_vvl_enable_high_load_threshold
EOL Comment: HIGH LOAD: When the load is above this threshold\, use the high load thresholds.

Name: CAL_vvl_disable_high_load_threshold
EOL Comment: HIGH LOAD: When the load is below this threshold\, use the normal thresholds.

Name: CAL_sensor_engine_air_scaling
EOL Comment:
Scaling of the engine air temperature sensor.

If use tmap = 0: The air temperature sensor from maf is used.
If use tmap = 1: The air temperature sensor from map is used.

Name: CAL_sensor_coolant_scaling
EOL Comment: Scaling of the engine coolant temperature sensor.

Name: CAL_sensor_intake_air_scaling
EOL Comment: Scaling of the air temperature sensor. Build into the maf.

Name: CAL_sensor_O2_scaling
EOL Comment: Scaling of the both oxygen (lambda) sensors.

Name: CAL_inj_time_base
EOL Comment:
Injector dead time.

Formula:

a = (load / (afr_base - afr_adj)) - evap
b = a / (efficiency * flow_rate)
c = b * adj1 * adj2 * adj3 + tip_in + tip_out + reactive
d = BASE + ltft_idle + (1 + stft + 2 * ltft) * c

inj_time = d

Name: CAL_ign_advance_cranking
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance (degree before top dead center) when cranking.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = ADVANCE_CRANKING

Name: CAL_injtip_catalyst_adj
EOL Comment:
During DFSO the catalyst is oxidized. Add extra fuel (injection time) to reactivate the catalyst.

Formula: reactivate = (time_base * ADJ) * (adj_fadeout ^ t)

Name: CAL_ign_advance_idle_adj1_alternative
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance idle adjustment.

Note: The ignition adj1_alternative will be used instead of adj1\, when the car is below the idle_flow_adj5_threshold speed.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + ADJ1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + ADJ1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj2
EOL Comment:
Compute the needed engine power (air flow) to keep a stabilized idling.

Formula: flow = flow_base + learned_adj1 - ADJ2 + adj3 + (adj4 * adj4_adj) + adj5 + adj6 + adj7 + adj8 + adj_ac + adj_fan_low + adj_fan_high - evap_flow

Note: adj8 is a dynamic adjustment.

Name: CAL_sensor_fuel_scaling
EOL Comment: Scaling of the fuel level sensor.

Name: CAL_closedloop_min_runtime
EOL Comment: The engine has to be running at least this amount of time\, before the closed loop operation can be activated.

Name: CAL_vvt_advance_low_cam_base
EOL Comment:
Intake camshaft advance when vvl is disengaged.

Formula: advance = BASE - adj

Name: CAL_vvt_advance_adj
EOL Comment:
Intake camshaft advance adjustment.

Formula: advance = base - ADJ

Name: CAL_inj_time_adj1
EOL Comment:
Fueling adjustment at startup. It's like a carburetor choke. The last line should always be 100%.

Formula:

a = (load / (afr_base - afr_adj)) - evap
b = a / (efficiency * flow_rate)
c = b * ADJ1 * adj2 * adj3 + tip_in + tip_out + reactive
d = base + ltft_idle + (1 + stft + 2 * ltft) * c

inj_time = d

Name: CAL_load_alphaN_engine_stop
EOL Comment:
Initial alphaN load calculation for cranking.

Formula: load = BASE * (atmo_pressure / 1013mbar) * (298K / temp_engine_air)

Note: temp_engine_air in Kelvin degrees.

Name: CAL_inj_time_adj2
EOL Comment:
Fueling adjustment with the air temperature.

Formula:

a = (load / (afr_base - afr_adj)) - evap
b = a / (efficiency * flow_rate)
c = b * adj1 * ADJ2 * adj3 + tip_in + tip_out + reactive
d = base + ltft_idle + (1 + stft + 2 * ltft) * c

inj_time = d

Name: CAL_ign_advance_adj1
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance adjustement with the engine air temperature.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + ADJ1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + ADJ1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_idle_speed_base
EOL Comment:
Desired engine idle speed.

Formula: speed_target = SPEED_BASE + speed_adj + speed_adj_ac_on

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj4_adj
EOL Comment:
Compute the needed engine power (air flow) to keep a stabilized idling.

Formula: flow = flow_base + learned_adj1 - adj2 + adj3 + (adj4 * ADJ4_ADJ) + adj5 + adj6 + adj7 + adj8 + adj_ac + adj_fan_low + adj_fan_high - evap_flow

Note: adj8 is a dynamic adjustment.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj3
EOL Comment:
Compute the needed engine power (air flow) to keep a stabilized idling.

Formula: flow = flow_base + learned_adj1 - adj2 + ADJ3 + (adj4 * adj4_adj) + adj5 + adj6 + adj7 + adj8 + adj_ac + adj_fan_low + adj_fan_high - evap_flow

Note: adj8 is a dynamic adjustment.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj4
EOL Comment:
Compute the needed engine power (air flow) to keep a stabilized idling.

Formula: flow = flow_base + learned_adj1 - adj2 + adj3 + (ADJ4 * adj4_adj) + adj5 + adj6 + adj7 + adj8 + adj_ac + adj_fan_low + adj_fan_high - evap_flow

Note: adj8 is a dynamic adjustment.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj5
EOL Comment:
Compute the needed engine power (air flow) to keep a stabilized idling.

Formula: flow = flow_base + learned_adj1 - adj2 + adj3 + (adj4 * adj4_adj) + ADJ5 + adj6 + adj7 + adj8 + adj_ac + adj_fan_low + adj_fan_high - evap_flow

Note: adj8 is a dynamic adjustment.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj8_corr_step
EOL Comment:
When the engine speed is not equal to the speed_target\, adj8 will be corrected by this value.

Formula: flow_adj8 = flow_adj8 +/- flow_adj8_corr_step

Name: CAL_ign_advance_idle_base
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance (degree before top dead center) when the engine is idling.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = IDLE_BASE + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_ign_advance_idle_adj1
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance idle adjustment.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + IDLE_ADJ1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_ign_advance_idle_adj2
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance idle adjustment.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + IDLE_ADJ2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_injtip_in_adj1
EOL Comment:
Add extra fuel (injection time) based on positive change in the tps. It's like the accelerator pump of a carburator.

Formula: tip_in(t) = time_base * (dt_tps2 - (adj2 * t)) * ADJ1 * adj3 * adj_gear

Name: CAL_injtip_in_adj2
EOL Comment:
Add extra fuel (injection time) based on positive change in the tps. It's like the accelerator pump of a carburator.

This adjustment will reduce the effect over time (t).

Formula: tip_in(t) = time_base * (dt_tps2 - (ADJ2 * t)) * adj1 * adj3 * adj_gear

Name: CAL_injtip_in_adj3
EOL Comment:
Add extra fuel (injection time) based on positive change in the tps. It's like the accelerator pump of a carburator.

Formula: tip_in(t) = time_base * (dt_tps2 - (adj2 * t)) * adj1 * ADJ3 * adj_gear

Name: CAL_injtip_out_adj1
EOL Comment:
Add extra fuel (injection time) based on negative change in the tps.

Formula: tip_out(t) = time_base * (dt_tps2 - (adj2 * t)) * ADJ1 * adj3

Name: CAL_injtip_out_adj2
EOL Comment:
Add extra fuel (injection time) based on negative change in the tps.

This adjustment will reduce the effect over time (t).

Formula: tip_out(t) = time_base * (dt_tps2 - (ADJ2 * t)) * adj1 * adj3

Name: CAL_injtip_out_adj3
EOL Comment:
Add extra fuel (injection time) based on negative change in the tps.

This adjustment will reduce the effect over time (t).

Formula: tip_out(t) = time_base * (dt_tps2 - (adj2 * t)) * adj1 * ADJ3

Name: CAL_idle_tps
EOL Comment: Once the needed air flow to keep the engine idling is knowned\, the ECU must drive the throttle body to the according position. The differential air pressure over the throttle body is estimated.

Name: CAL_ign_advance_high_cam_base
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance (degree before top dead center) when the VVL is engaged and engine speed is below vvl_enable_rpm (by default 6200 RPM).

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = HIGH_CAM_BASE * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_enrichment_step
EOL Comment:
When a lean condition is detected\, the stft will enrich the mixture.

Formula (first)     : stft = stft + initial
Formula (subsequent): stft = stft + STEP
Formula (with adj)  : stft = stft + STEP * adj

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_enleanment_step
EOL Comment:
When a rich condition is detected\, the stft will enlean the mixture.

Formula (first)     : stft = stft - initial
Formula (subsequent): stft = stft - STEP
Formula (with adj)  : stft = stft - STEP * adj

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_enrichment_initial
EOL Comment:
When a lean condition is detected\, the stft will enrich the mixture.

Formula (first)     : stft = stft + INITIAL
Formula (subsequent): stft = stft + step
Formula (with adj)  : stft = stft + step * adj

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_enleanment_initial
EOL Comment:
When a rich condition is detected\, the stft will enlean the mixture.

Formula (first)     : stft = stft - INITIAL
Formula (subsequent): stft = stft - step
Formula (with adj)  : stft = stft - step * adj

Name: CAL_inj_efficiency
EOL Comment:
Injector efficiency. Depending on the fuel rail and the manifold pressure\, the efficiency of the injectors change.

Formula:

a = (load / (afr_base - afr_adj)) - evap
b = a / (EFFICIENCY * flow_rate)
c = b * adj1 * adj2 * adj3 + tip_in + tip_out + reactive
d = base + ltft_idle + (1 + stft + 2 * ltft) * c

inj_time = d

Name: CAL_vvt_advance_high_cam_base
EOL Comment:
Intake camshaft advance when vvl is engaged.

Formula: advance = BASE - adj

Name: CAL_load_possible_max
EOL Comment:
The engine load is also available as a ratio to the possible max load (OBD Mode 0x01 PID 0x04).

Formula: load(%) = load(mg/stroke) / LOAD_MAX * (1013mbar / atmo_pressure)

Name: CAL_tpssmooth_increment
EOL Comment: Throttle responsiveness when pressing the gas pedal.

Name: CAL_load_use_alphaN_tps_threshold
EOL Comment: When the tps is above this position threshold\, use the alphaN load calculation.

Name: CAL_inj_time_adj3
EOL Comment:
Fueling adjustment with the coolant temperature.

Formula:

a = (load / (afr_base - afr_adj)) - evap
b = a / (efficiency * flow_rate)
c = b * adj1 * adj2 * ADJ3 + tip_in + tip_out + reactive
d = base + ltft_idle + (1 + stft + 2 * ltft) * c

inj_time = d

Name: CAL_tc_slip_adj1
EOL Comment:
When the car is slipping the ecu apply a factor to the advance of the ignition. A retard to the ignition makes the engine loose torque.

Formula: ign_adv_adj = 100% - steps - (slip - ADJ1 - adj2) * slip_to_retard_ratio

Note: When using variable control knob: ADJ1 = (knob_position / 2^ADJ1)

Name: CAL_tc_fuelcut
EOL Comment:
Every # stroke will have no fuel. The value 255 means no fuel cut.

Example: 8 means that 1 of 8 strokes will have no fuel.

Name: CAL_ign_advance_high_cam_knock_safe
EOL Comment: Knock safe ignition advance used by knock_retard2.

Name: CAL_idle_tps_engine_stop
EOL Comment: Throttle body position for cranking.

Name: CAL_ecu_shutdown_delay
EOL Comment: HEAT SOAK: How long should the ECU running after turning the key on the OFF position.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj_ac
EOL Comment:
WITH A/C ON: Compensate the power of the A/C compressor.

Formula: flow = flow_base + learned_adj1 - ADJ2 + adj3 + (adj4 * adj4_adj) + adj5 + adj6 + adj7 + adj8 + ADJ_AC + adj_fan_low + adj_fan_high - evap_flow

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj_fan_low
EOL Comment:
WITH FAN LOW ON: Compensate the power of the low speed fan.

Formula: flow = flow_base + learned_adj1 - ADJ2 + adj3 + (adj4 * adj4_adj) + adj5 + adj6 + adj7 + adj8 + adj_ac + ADJ_FAN_LOW + adj_fan_high - evap_flow

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj_fan_high
EOL Comment:
WITH FAN HIGH ON: Compensate the power of the high speed fan.

Formula: flow = flow_base + learned_adj1 - ADJ2 + adj3 + (adj4 * adj4_adj) + adj5 + adj6 + adj7 + adj8 + adj_ac + adj_low_fan + ADJ_HIGH_FAN - evap_flow

Name: CAL_inj_time_adj_cranking
EOL Comment:
Fueling adjustment when cranking.

Formula: inj_time = base + adj_cranking

Name: CAL_idle_speed_adj
EOL Comment:
Desired engine idle speed.

Formula: speed_target = speed_base + SPEED_ADJ + speed_adj_ac_on

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj6
EOL Comment:
Compute the needed engine power (air flow) to keep a stabilized idling.

Formula: flow = flow_base + learned_adj1 - adj2 + adj3 + (adj4 * adj4_adj) + adj5 + ADJ6 + adj7 + adj8 + adj_ac + adj_fan_low + adj_fan_high - evap_flow

Note: adj8 is a dynamic adjustment.

Name: CAL_inj_angle
EOL Comment: Target engine position to begin fuel injection (with an offset for each cylinder's relative position).

Name: CAL_dfso_delay
EOL Comment: A delay is used before activating deceleration fuel shut off.

Name: CAL_ign_advance_adj2
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance adjustement for startup.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * ADJ2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * ADJ2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_ign_time_base
EOL Comment: Spark firing length.

Name: CAL_ign_advance_low_cam_knock_safe
EOL Comment: Knock safe ignition advance used by knock_retard2.

Name: CAL_ign_advance_low_cam_base
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance (degree before top dead center) when the VVL is disengaged or when engine speed is above vvl_enable_rpm (by default 6200 RPM).

Formula (low cam) : adv = LOW_CAM_BASE * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_sensor_maf_scaling
EOL Comment: Scaling of the mass air flow sensor.

Name: CAL_idle_flow_adj7
EOL Comment:
Compute the needed engine power (air flow) to keep a stabilized idling.

Formula: flow = flow_base + learned_adj1 - adj2 + adj3 + (adj4 * adj4_adj) + adj5 + adj6 + ADJ7 + adj8 + adj_ac + adj_fan_low + adj_fan_high - evap_flow

Note: adj8 is a dynamic adjustment.

Name: CAL_tpssmooth_decrement
EOL Comment: Throttle responsiveness when releasing the gas pedal.

Name: CAL_ign_advance_adj3
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance adjustement with the engine speed.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (ADJ3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (ADJ3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_ign_advance_adj3_adj
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance adjustement with the engine speed.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * ADJ3_ADJ) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * ADJ3_ADJ) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_ign_advance_idle_adj3
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance idle adjustment.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + adj4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + IDLE_ADJ3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_vvt_min_runtime
EOL Comment: The engine has to be running at least this amount of time\, before the vvt can be engaged.

Name: CAL_closedloop_stft_time_use_adj
EOL Comment: If all corrections after this amount of time are insufficient\, the step value is adjusted.

Name: CAL_ign_advance_adj4
EOL Comment:
Ignition advance adjustement with the change in the tps.

Formula (low cam) : adv = low_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + ADJ4
Formula (high cam): adv = high_cam_base * adj2 * tc_adj + adj1 + (adj3 * adj3_adj) + ADJ4
Formula (idle)    : adv = idle_base + idle_adj1 + idle_adj2 + idle_adj3 + idle_adj_ac_on
Formula (dfso)    : adv = advance_dfso
Formula (cranking): adv = advance_cranking

Name: CAL_knock_sensitivity_cylinder1
EOL Comment: Knock sensitivity cylinder 1 value send to the L9119D.

Name: CAL_knock_sensitivity_cylinder2
EOL Comment: Knock sensitivity cylinder 2 value send to the L9119D.

Name: CAL_knock_sensitivity_cylinder3
EOL Comment: Knock sensitivity cylinder 3 value send to the L9119D.

Name: CAL_knock_sensitivity_cylinder4
EOL Comment: Knock sensitivity cylinder 4 value send to the L9119D.

Name: CAL_knock_peak_threshold
EOL Comment:
When the peak is above this threshold\, the ECU takes it as a real knock.

Formula:

signal_avg = (100% - reactivity) * signal_avg + reactivity * signal
peak = (signal * 10) / (signal_avg + 1)
peak_over_threshold = peak - THRESHOLD

Name: CAL_knock_retard1_step
EOL Comment:
Increment retard1 in proportion to the knock peak.

Formula (per cylinder): retard1 = retard1 + STEP

Name: CAL_knock_retard_threshold
EOL Comment:
The ECU will apply the retard1 and the retard2 values\, if the engine is above this load threshold.

If the load is below this threshold minus the load_margin\, the retard1 is reset to 0 and the retard2 is not more applied.

Formula (per cylinder): retard = RETARD1 + (ign_advance_xxx_cam_base - ign_advance_xxx_cam_knock_safe) * RETARD2

Name: CAL_knock_retard2_corr_threshold
EOL Comment:
The ECU will make corrections to the retard2 value\, if the engine is above this load threshold.

If the load is below this threshold minus the load_margin\, no more corrections will occur.

Formula (per cylinder): retard = RETARD1 + (ign_advance_xxx_cam_base - ign_advance_xxx_cam_knock_safe) * RETARD2

Name: CAL_evap_purge
EOL Comment:
The evap purge valve is normally closed.

Formula: opening = duty_cylce_min + PURGE

Name: CAL_misc_tps
EOL Comment: Target tps position for a given pps position.

Name: CAL_misc_coolant_warning_threshold
EOL Comment: When the engine coolant is above this temperature threshold\, display the warning on the instrument cluster.

Name: CAL_sensor_evap_reactivity
EOL Comment:
At every cycle\, the sampled evaporative value is mixed with the previous value.

Formula: value = (100% - REACTIVITY) * previous + REACTIVITY * sample

Name: CAL_obd2_warm_up_cycles_clear_freeze_frame
EOL Comment: Number of warm-up cycles before erasing the freeze frame.

Name: CAL_obd2_P0133_threshold1_rich2lean
EOL Comment: P0133 Threshold 1: Throws an error code when both the lean-to-rich and RICH-TO-LEAN transitions exceed their respective time thresholds.

Name: CAL_obd2_P0133_threshold1_lean2rich
EOL Comment: P0133 Threshold 1: Throws an error code when both the LEAN-TO-RICH and rich-to-lean transitions exceed their respective time thresholds.

Name: CAL_obd2_P0133_threshold2_lean2rich
EOL Comment: P0133 Threshold 2: With a ratio threshold of 200% and a TIME threshold of 135ms\, this means that if the lean-to-rich transition is twice as slow as the rich-to-lean transition and takes more than 135ms\, it will trigger an error code.

Name: CAL_obd2_P0133_threshold3_rich2lean
EOL Comment: P0133 Threshold 3: With a ratio threshold of 50% and a TIME threshold of 70ms\, this means that if the rich-to-lean transition is twice as slow as the lean-to-rich transition and takes more than 70ms\, it will trigger an error code.

Name: CAL_sensor_O2_heater_threshold
EOL Comment: The electrical resistance of the O2 sensor heater increases with temperature. The ECU will stop the heater when the current drop below this current threshold.

Name: CAL_obd2_P0133_threshold2_ratio
EOL Comment: P0133 Threshold 2: With a RATIO threshold of 200% and a time threshold of 135ms\, this means that if the lean-to-rich transition is twice as slow as the rich-to-lean transition and takes more than 135ms\, it will trigger an error code.

Name: CAL_obd2_P0133_threshold3_ratio
EOL Comment: P0133 Threshold 3: With a RATIO threshold of 50% and a time threshold of 70ms\, this means that if the rich-to-lean transition is twice as slow as the lean-to-rich transition and takes more than 70ms\, it will trigger an error code.

EOL Comment: Number of consecutive occurrences before raising the trouble code.

Name: CAL_load_alphaN_base
EOL Comment:
Rapid changes in tps create too much turbulence to have a reliable maf information. So the ECU falls back into a traditional alphaN load calculation for a small amount of time.

An absolute tps position threshold also trigger the usage of the alphaN table.

Formula: load = BASE * (atmo_pressure / 1013mbar) * (298K / temp_engine_air) * learned_adj

Note: temp_engine_air in Kelvin degrees.

Name: CAL_inj_afr_base
EOL Comment:
Ratio between air and fuel.

Formula:

a = (load / (AFR_BASE - afr_adj)) - evap
b = a / (efficiency * flow_rate)
c = b * adj1 * adj2 * adj3 + tip_in + tip_out + reactive
d = base + ltft_idle + (1 + stft + 2 * ltft) * c

inj_time = d

Name: CAL_obd2_P0128_air_mass_factor
EOL Comment: In a certain condition\, a factor is applied to the air mass calculation before being compared with the wait air mass value.

Name: CAL_obd2_P0128_wait_air_mass
EOL Comment: Wait for a certain amount of air to enter the engine before evaluating whether the thermostat is stuck open with the P0128 threshold value.

Name: CAL_ecu_unlock_magic
EOL Comment: Unlocked ECU have a read/write access through CAN-Bus (Live-Tuning).
